                <note rend="inline" type="source">812.0144/169: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Chihuahua</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stewart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chihuahua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-09-05T12:00:00-07:04">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 5, 1919, noon</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received 6 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>For the third time since August 28th two American air planes flew over city this
                    morning causing embarrassment to members of the American colony because of
                    frequency of flights. Will make no further reports unless instructed. Embassy
                    advised.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stewart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
